# astra8_mas_wetware.v — translate_off Hot-Comment Fix
# =============================================================================
#
# PROBLEM:
#   rtl/astra8/astra8_mas_wetware.v line 50 uses the legacy hot-comment:
#
#       // translate_off
#       ... simulation-only code ...
#       // translate_on
#
#   Yosys warns about this:
#       "Warning: Encountered `translate_off' comment! Such legacy
#        hot comments are supported by Yosys, but are not part of any
#        formal language specification. Using a portable and
#        standards-compliant construct such as `ifdef is recommended!"
#
#   This is not a fatal error, but it's a professional polish issue.
#   Some commercial tools (older Synopsys, Cadence) treat these
#   hot-comments inconsistently. The portable, standards-compliant
#   replacement is the `ifdef SIMULATION directive.
#
# FIX:
#   Replace every:
#       // translate_off
#           ... sim-only code ...
#       // translate_on
#
#   With:
#       `ifdef SIMULATION
#           ... sim-only code ...
#       `endif
#
#   Then define `SIMULATION` only in your simulation flow (Icarus,
#   Verilator, Modelsim), not in synthesis flow (Yosys, Vivado synth).
#
# HOW TO APPLY:
#   1. Open rtl/astra8/astra8_mas_wetware.v
#   2. Find every `// translate_off` and `// translate_on` pair
#   3. Replace per the fix above
#   4. Add `-DSIMULATION` to your Icarus/Verilator invocation:
#          iverilog -g2012 -DSIMULATION -I rtl ...
#      Or in cocotb Makefile:
#          COMPILE_ARGS += -DSIMULATION
#   5. Do NOT add -DSIMULATION to Yosys/Vivado synth commands.
#
# AUTOMATED SEARCH:
#   To find every file that uses translate_off in your repo:
#
#       grep -rn "translate_off" rtl/
#       grep -rn "translate_on"  rtl/
#
# SED ONE-LINER (apply to a single file):
#
#   sed -i \
#       -e 's|^\(\s*\)//\s*translate_off.*$|\1`ifdef SIMULATION|' \
#       -e 's|^\(\s*\)//\s*translate_on.*$|\1`endif|' \
#       rtl/astra8/astra8_mas_wetware.v
#
#   (Inspect with `git diff` afterwards.)
#
# =============================================================================

# Example "before" snippet (around line 50 of astra8_mas_wetware.v):
#
#   // translate_off
#   always @(*) begin
#       // simulation-only behavioral model
#       chem_v[idx] = $random;
#       chem_u[idx] = $random;
#   end
#   // translate_on
#

# Example "after" snippet:
#
#   `ifdef SIMULATION
#   always @(*) begin
#       // simulation-only behavioral model
#       chem_v[idx] = $random;
#       chem_u[idx] = $random;
#   end
#   `endif
#

# =============================================================================
# WHY THIS MATTERS FOR IP SALE
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Removes 50+ Yosys warnings → cleaner synthesis log
# 2. Removes "amateur" signal from synth reports (buyers DO read these)
# 3. Makes your RTL portable across Yosys, Vivado, Quartus, VCS, Xcelium,
#    Modelsim, Verilator — every tool understands `ifdef
# 4. Standardizes the codebase to industry convention
#
# =============================================================================
